# yakircohen.com — Project Rules

## Stack

- Next.js 16.2.6 (App Router) + React 19 + TypeScript 5
- Tailwind CSS v4 (PostCSS plugin only — no classic `tailwind.config.js`)
- Pagefind for search (build-time)
- Vercel (production), GitHub Actions CI

## Architecture

- `app/` — all pages (App Router)
- `components/` — shared UI
- `hooks/` — custom hooks
- `lib/` — utilities (includes `legacy-redirects`)
- `public/` — static assets
- `scripts/` — audit scripts (images, links, headings, pagefind)

## Never

- Add `"use client"` unless required — Server Components by default
- Use `pages/` router — everything under `app/`
- Add `tailwind.config.js` — Tailwind v4 is PostCSS-only
- Change `next.config.ts` without explicit approval — security headers and redirects live there
- Put secrets in code — Vercel env vars only
- Remove or rename `RESEND_API_KEY` / `LEAD_NOTIFY_EMAIL` from env docs or usage

## Always

- New pages: `generateMetadata()` with title, description, and OG
- Images: Next.js `<Image>` (not raw `<img>`), except where an existing pattern intentionally uses `<img>` (e.g. lazy YouTube thumbnails)
- External links: `target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"`
- Before commit: `npm run lint` and `npm run build` (or `build:full` when search/index changes)
- Commit messages: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `docs:` prefixes

## Environment (Vercel production)

- `RESEND_API_KEY` — Resend email API
- `LEAD_NOTIFY_EMAIL` — lead notifications (e.g. callwebboss@gmail.com)

## API

- `app/api/lead-notify/route.ts` — email on form submit; requires both env vars above

## Build scripts

- `npm run dev` — local dev
- `npm run build` — standard build
- `npm run build:full` — build + Pagefind (Vercel `vercel-build`)
- `npm run lint` — required before commit
- `npm run audit:images` / `audit:links` — asset and link checks
- `npm run check:youtube` — validate YouTube video IDs

## Domain & deploy

- Production: https://yakircohen.com
- Preview only: yakircohen-com.vercel.app (do not share with clients)
- Push to `main` → Vercel auto-deploy
- GitHub Actions runs lint + build — do not force-push to `main` if CI fails
